\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Rolling-concurrency example with \(N=2\), \(K=2\), and \(p_I=60\) seconds. Waiting is measured only for image \(I\) availability; useful runtime is shown to explain when the next queued job can start.}}{8}{table.caption.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:rolling-example}{{2}{8}{Rolling-concurrency example with \(N=2\), \(K=2\), and \(p_I=60\) seconds. Waiting is measured only for image \(I\) availability; useful runtime is shown to explain when the next queued job can start}{table.caption.5}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Rolling-concurrency example. Jobs \(J_1\) and \(J_2\) both wait a full \(p_I=60\) seconds on \(N_0\). Job \(J_4\) starts while image \(I\) is still unavailable on \(N_1\) and waits only the remaining 30 seconds until \(T_{N_1}(I)\).}}{8}{figure.caption.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:rolling-node-timeline}{{4}{8}{Rolling-concurrency example. Jobs \(J_1\) and \(J_2\) both wait a full \(p_I=60\) seconds on \(N_0\). Job \(J_4\) starts while image \(I\) is still unavailable on \(N_1\) and waits only the remaining 30 seconds until \(T_{N_1}(I)\)}{figure.caption.6}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Comparison of the same deterministic example under all three modes. The rolling case is a time-aware operational case between the sequential and full-burst analytical references. Each full block represents one \(p_I=60\) second image wait; the half block represents a 30 second remaining wait.}}{9}{figure.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:rolling-boundary-check}{{5}{9}{Comparison of the same deterministic example under all three modes. The rolling case is a time-aware operational case between the sequential and full-burst analytical references. Each full block represents one \(p_I=60\) second image wait; the half block represents a 30 second remaining wait}{figure.caption.7}{}}
